# EMSTrainer License

Copyright © 2025 Joel

## Mission Statement

EMSTrainer is built to improve the pipeline of EMS professionals and benefit emergency medical services across the country. This license reflects that mission by keeping the software free for individual learners and educators while enabling sustainable development through institutional licensing.

## License Terms

This software is dual-licensed:

### 1. Free Educational Use (Individuals & Small Groups)

**FREE for:**
- Individual EMS students studying for certification
- Individual instructors teaching their own students
- Small volunteer departments (≤5 users)
- Personal study and practice
- Non-profit educational use

**Terms:** Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 (CC BY-NC 4.0)
- ✅ Share and adapt the material
- ✅ Use for teaching and learning
- ✅ Provide attribution to EMSTrainer
- ❌ No commercial use without license

Full CC BY-NC 4.0 text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/

### 2. Institutional License (Academic Institutions & Organizations)

**REQUIRES PAID LICENSE for:**
- Community colleges and universities
- EMS training academies
- Hospital-based training programs
- Commercial training companies
- Fire departments with formal training programs (>5 users)
- Any organization using EMSTrainer as part of paid coursework or certification programs

**Why?** Institutional licensing fees support ongoing development, medical accuracy validation, scenario creation, and keeping the software free for individual students.

**Institutional License Benefits:**
- Unlimited student use within your institution
- Priority support and bug fixes
- Custom scenario development assistance
- Instructor training and onboarding
- Integration support
- Influence on feature roadmap

**Pricing:** Contact for institutional licensing rates

### 3. Commercial License

**REQUIRES PAID LICENSE for:**
- Incorporation into commercial products
- Resale or redistribution for profit
- Use in for-profit training offerings
- Any commercial use not covered above

## Licensing Inquiries

For institutional or commercial licensing:
- **GitHub Issues:** https://github.com/jj33/EMSTrainer/issues
- Tag your issue with `[LICENSING]` in the title
- Include: Organization name, number of users, intended use
- We'll respond within 2-3 business days

## Enforcement

Unauthorized commercial or institutional use violates this license and applicable copyright law. We prefer to work with organizations to find appropriate licensing arrangements.

## Contributing

Contributions to EMSTrainer are welcome! By contributing, you agree that your contributions will be licensed under the same terms as the project.

## Disclaimer

THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" FOR EDUCATIONAL PURPOSES ONLY. NOT A SUBSTITUTE FOR OFFICIAL EMS PROTOCOLS, MEDICAL DIRECTION, OR HANDS-ON TRAINING. USE AT YOUR OWN RISK.

